==English==
===Etymology===
Probably from ''[[easter]]'' + ''[[-ly]]''

===Noun===
'''easterly'''
# ([[Meteorology]]) Any [[persistent]] wind from the east (usually applied to broad currents or belts of easterly
winds). The easterly belts are referred to as the [[equatorial easterlies]], the [[tropical easterlies]], and the [[polar easterlies]].


[[Category:English nouns]]

===Adjective===
'''easterly'''
#Facing the east; directed towards the east.
#Located towards the east.
====Derived terms====
*[[easterliness]]

[[Category:English adjectives]]

===Adverb===
'''easterly'''
#In an [[eastward]] direction or position; towards the east.
#From the east.

[[Category:English adverbs]]

